HEADWORD: Fiord
<hw>Fiord</hw> <pr>(fy<?/rd; <it>i</it> or <it>y</it> consonant,
⟦sect⟧ 272)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dan. & Norw. <ets>fiord</ets>. See
<er>Frith</er>.]</ety> <def>A narrow inlet of the sea, penetrating
between high banks or rocks, as on the coasts of Norway and
Alaska.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>fjord</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fiorin</ent>⟦br⟧
